cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.COMM, cs.SY, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper focuses on interference modeling and capacity coverage analysis in cellular networks, which falls under the domain of networking and internet architecture. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper discusses the distribution of intercell interference in the downlink of cellular networks, which involves the study of information transmission and processing. 
3. cs.COMM (Communication and Networking) - The paper deals with interference and scheduling in cellular networks, which are key topics in communication and networking. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper presents an analytical approach for modeling interference in cellular networks, which can be viewed as a system control problem. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper discusses location-based and average-based data rates in cellular networks, which are relevant to multimedia applications.
